ion-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Desmoid Tumor<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-8788e3d elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"8788e3d\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-50362f7\" data-id=\"50362f7\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-6ee2697 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"6ee2697\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>General<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Fibroblastic Tumor of Fascial &amp; Aponeurotic Connective Tissue<\/li><li><strong>Benign with No Mets<\/strong><\/li><li>Locally Aggressive with <strong>High Local Recurrence<\/strong> (30%)<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Location<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Intraabdominal \u2013 Most are Unresectable at Time of Diagnosis<\/li><li>Extraabdominal<ul><li>Most Common Site: Anterior Abdominal Wall (Often Following Pregnancy or Trauma)<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Associations<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Most Are Sporadic<ul><li>Most Common Mutation: CTNNB1<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Repeated Trauma to an Area or Surgery (Seen Along a Scar)<\/li><li>FAP\/Gardner\u2019s Syndrome (APC Mutation)<ul><li><a href=\"http:\/\/operativereview.com\/colorectal-cancer-and-polyposis-syndromes\/\">*See Oncology: Colorectal Cancer &amp; Polyposis Syndromes<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>CT: Depends on Composition<ul><li>Can be Homogenous or Heterogenous<\/li><li>Can by Hypointense or Hyperintense<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Core Needle Bx (Histology): <strong>Spindle Cells<\/strong>, <strong>Dense Fibrosis<\/strong>, High Cellularity &amp; Low Mitotic Index<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>General Treatment: Surgical Resection<ul><li>Can Observe if Asymptomatic &amp; Stable in Size<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Unresectable: XRT or Chemo (Tamoxifen &amp; Sulindac)<\/li><li>Consider <strong>Colonoscopy<\/strong> to Evaluate FAP<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-elemen